reviews.review_text: I got hungry and put  tacos  into my google maps and I THANKFULLY was brought here. The menu has pictures and descriptions of everything but I knew I wanted tacos. I was thrilled to be charged only $20 for 4 tacos and a Jarrito. The tacos were beautiful and delicious - exactly what I wanted. I read through other reviews and I m confused how someone could complain! I am definitely coming back here again. Kid-friendliness: They sell Mexican candy and toys at very low prices! Need I say more?

Found them on Instagram and were super excited to have an authentic Mexican restaurant close to our place. We also love the idea of supporting a small, local business. To start, the service was wonderful. We were helped in good time, assisted with menu options, and had a nice little chat at the end of our visit. The restaurant itself is super cute! Bar style seating with lots of beautiful decorations. Now, to the best part, the food ! I ordered the enchiladas papas, which is their Mexican enchiladas with grilled potatoes that are cooked with onions as the filling. As a vegetarian I was stoked to see that they had 4 different options for fillings that could replace meat. The portions were great as were the flavors. I topped it with a little bit of Pico de Gallo and one of the (many!) sauces they have available. I also really liked that they had the sauces on ice for freshness! My boyfriend ordered 4 asada tacos with a side of Pico de Gallo. He commented that the meat was cooked perfectly, Pico was on point and everything tasted fresh. Portions were also perfect. We both would consider Mexican food as our favorite cuisine and while we arent experts in the authenticity (maybe a trip to Mexico is finally in order!) we have eaten at ALOT of Mexican restaurants in Vancouver and can confidently say that Taco N Todo is one of the best by far. Vegetarian options: They had 4 options for vegetarian filling. They can substitute easily! Parking: Paid street parking is available out front along Fraser street. There are also pay parking lots across the street in the alley.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your comments. It is always nice to hear about happy costumers. Thank you for your comments, that allow us to improve our next service. Gracias!

reviews.review_text: Today I tried Mexican food for the first time.  we chose this restaurant for our first lunch.  I made a mistake and did not say that we would like spicy food and then a very attentive woman said that she wanted us to try the real taste of Mexican food!  and treated us to another dish for free.  very nice such attention and attitude!  will definitely come again for real mexican food  thanks, very good service!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Heh Julia. Nice to hear from you! Thank you so much I am very glad and happy we accomplished the goal! That you really taste what you really wanted! It such a great feeling I got a new happy customer. Thank you to come close to the counter and being honest about your thoughts in the right moment. I think is the best time to really know what our customers are thinking and serve you better! Muchas gracias. Pleasure to meet you. Monica/Owner

reviews.review_text: Yesssss finally found a restaurant with proper Mexican food I felt like i was still in Los Cabos. The service was good. Food came fast. Definitely will come here again and again.
This place is awesome! Ordered  a burrito wrap and coffee. The coffee is sooo good I had to order a second cup! The burrito was delicious!! Definitley want to go back!

Small. Authentic Mexican experience. I had the person taking my order to surprise me, and for her to choose. All three different tacos were great. Excellent value by local standards. Three tacos were a full meal. Bigger than most and more fillings per taco than most taco places. Two larger tortillas per taco. I would prefer more spicy, but I like it very spicy. I highly recommend this restaurant.

We come to the area often, but usually for Chinese food. Dropped in today at spouses suggestion. Good call. Great food (fresh and tasty). Good prices. Nice and friendly staff. Will come back for sure!!!

The food here is great! The meat is juicy & flavourful. The beef taco was sooo good Id definitely recommend that and the beans. The beans were shockingly good, so creamy & well balanced in flavour. Lots of fresh, yummy options on the menu and for a good price!

reviews.review_text: I don t understand how people come to this restaurants website only to leave a bad review to attempt to bring negativity to their business. The customer service was so respectful and polite. I ordered the  Al Pastor  Tacos that were beautiful and delicious, such great flavour. I came here on the very first week they opened and i will say it was a bit slow, but it is completely understandable if the business had just started. I came back for a second shot and the service improved massively, the orders were being received at a good speed, and the food is totally worth it. Taco N Todo I am truly sorry for the negativity people can take out because i m sure it is at least once daily. Great food. Will come back to try everything! Vegetarian options: Lots of multiple good vegetarian options. Haven t tried them but there s plenty!

reviews.review_text: We hired TacoN Todo to serve up tacos for a late night snack at our wedding this summer and they were amazing! reviews.review_text: A nice, decent Mexican restaurant situated on Fraser St. Quality of the food is alright, but not the best I ve had. There s a lot of fierce competition out there that would deliver more on flavor and value. Overall atmosphere of the place is nice, service was a little slow given that there was only one person making and assembling the food, I do hope they will bring on board more staff to help out! Maybe I caught them on a bad day? Menu looked a bit disorganized, cramped,  and a little too unnecessarily complicated to read. Food overall was average. The meat was tasty, but like the other reviews; it is a little dry. The tortilla s weren t well heated either, though that can be easily fixed by asking for it to toast a bit more. Price-wise it s a bit expensive for the quality being churned out. Sauces and condiments are pretty nice. Standard Valentino sauce, salsa verde. Wish they had some more choices! I want to support this restaurant. There s a lot of potential here, but it needs work. I hope there s a talented restaurant marketer or consultant they can reach out to help them. We need more Mexican restaurants in vancouver!

reviews.review_text: First time trying this taco shop. I would say it was okay. I enjoyed 3 of the 5 tacos. I ordered 4 tacos and 1 chori asada taco. The chicken, beef, and pork tasted fine, but for the chori asada taco was dry and not seasoned well. The vegetarian taco was not IT for me. I also thought the tortillas felt cold and ripped easily. I plan to try again to see if things improve.

Authentic Mexican food. Friendly counter person and cook. Mexican candy and drinks too. My food was too hot    for me to finish. I dont like super hot or spicy food. On a scale from 1 to 10, I give this place a 5. If you like heat and Mexican food, this is the place for you.
